{SECT 0 {PARA 258 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 15 "Hong, Sunghyuck" }}{PARA 258 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 9 "4/28/2003" }}{PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT 256 34 "Introd
uction to Graphing Functions" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 179 "Save your current worksheet as work04-yourlast
name.mws.  Remember to save frequently to avoid losing data in case th
at the system would shut down in the middle of a work session! " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 104 "In the t
ext mode (click on the cap T button) place your name(s) and date at th
e top of your worksheet.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 31 "1.  Graphing func
tions and the " }{TEXT 257 4 "plot" }{TEXT -1 89 " command.  The Maple
 command for plotting the graph of an explicitly defined function is:
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     \+
" }{TEXT 258 0 "" }{TEXT 259 4 "plot" }{TEXT 260 0 "" }{TEXT -1 2 "( \+
" }{TEXT 261 4 "expr" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 266 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 20 "
=range [, options]);" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 6 "where " }{TEXT 262 4 "expr" }{TEXT 267 1 " " }{TEXT -1 
24 "is a symbolic expression" }{TEXT 264 1 " " }{TEXT -1 48 "which rep
resents the function to be plotted and " }{TEXT 263 1 "x" }{TEXT -1 
38 " is the independent variable used in  " }{TEXT 265 4 "expr" }
{TEXT -1 25 "  to define the function." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 81 "Several options exist to change way t
he plot will appear.  These options include:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 126 "            y=range           \+
            this allows the user to specifiy the range of output value
s which Maple will display" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 113 "          \+
  thickness=value           this controls the thickness of the plotted
 curve.  value = 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 119 "   \+
         color=value                 this sets the color of the plotte
d curve.  value = red, green, blue, cyan, etc." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 160 "For each of the followin
g functions provide a plot to represent the graph the function.  Choos
e a range that will optimally represent the features of the graph." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 16 "a.    y =
 3x - 1" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "b.    " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "y = 6*x
^2+24*x-8;" "6#/%\"yG,(*&\"\"'\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"#F(F(*&\"#CF(F*F(F(\"\"
)!\"\"" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "
c.   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "y = ((1+x)/(1-x))^(1/2);" "6#/%\"yG)*&,&\"\"\"F
(%\"xGF(F(,&F(F(F)!\"\"F+*&F(F(\"\"#F+" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "d.  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 
"y = exp(-x^2)/(1+x^2);" "6#/%\"yG*&-%$expG6#,$*$%\"xG\"\"#!\"\"\"\"\"
,&F.F.*$F+F,F.F-" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "f1:=3*x-1;" 
}}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#f1G,&*&\"\"$\"\"\"%\"xGF(F(F(!\"
\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "f2:=6*x^2-24*x-8;" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#f2G,(*&\"\"'\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"#F(F(*&
\"#CF(F*F(!\"\"\"\")F." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "f
